         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
                  <D_OUTSIDE_SCOPE/>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>The University applied to the National Institute of Health Research for the establishment of an NIHR Global Health Research Unit, which has been subsequently awarded. The overarching Hub Agreement sets out the broad roles and responsibilities to be delivered by the collaborating institution/hospital as a NIHR Global Surgery Hub, but it does not replace intended contracts for delivery of specific trials, which will be produced and disseminated separately upon approval from the University and NIHR. Following discussions with certain hospitals in low and middle income countries, contracts (that comply with contractual agreement between UoB and NIHR) will be signed with the collaborating institutions/hospitals to carry out the work as envisaged in the application awarded by the funding body and those that are developed through annual prioritisation cycles. Prior to the funding being awarded support was given by various clinicians in the respective countries, which offered collaboration upon award. Post award, the University will establish at least 5 overseas Hubs from the supporting bodies (West Africa, Southern Africa, Central &amp; East Africa, Central and South America, Asia) to extend research from at least 40 LMIC research Spokes into impact across 230 + network hospitals. Contracts have already been signed by the hospitals noted and the other hospital Hubs will be added from the designated areas as contracts are agreed.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
